episodes.title: Members Only
episodes.plot: Gene Pontecorvo makes a final break from the mob life, while Junior's paranoid delusions could be the end of Tony.

episodes.title: Join the Club
episodes.plot: The family tries to cope with Tony's hospitalization and deteriorating condition, while Tony begins to hallucinate a new life parallel to his own.

episodes.title: Mayham
episodes.plot: While the gang begins to turn on itself, Tony finds himself at the threshold, while Christopher gives another try to enter the movie business, however this time as a producer rather than a screenwriter.

episodes.title: The Fleshy Part of the Thigh
episodes.plot: Tony goes home and returns to business, perhaps with a new frame of mind. Paulie receives a shock about his mother.

episodes.title: Mr. & Mrs. John Sacrimoni Request
episodes.plot: Johnny Sack is granted permission to attend his daughter's wedding. Tony improves his personal security and Vito's secret double life is exposed.

episodes.title: Live Free or Die
episodes.plot: Tony hires help from overseas to fulfill a favor he was asked for by Johnny Sack and decides if one of his top earners deserves a second chance as he acknowledges to Dr. Melfi he was given a second chance when he survived his gun shot wound.

episodes.title: Luxury Lounge
episodes.plot: Christopher and Carmine travel to Hollywood to take the next step in making their movie but quickly realize they're out of their depth. Artie feuds with Benny after his restaurant falls prey to one of Tony's scams.

episodes.title: Johnny Cakes
episodes.plot: Vito considers starting a new life in New Hampshire, while Anthony Jr. looking for a purpose and finds it when he continues his pursuit of revenge against Junior.

episodes.title: The Ride
episodes.plot: Paulie finds public opinion turned against him after an amusement ride accident. Christopher tries to start a new life as a husband and father.

episodes.title: Moe n' Joe
episodes.plot: Tony reflects on how growing up with Janice colors his attitudes now, while Vito tries to make a new life for himself in New Hampshire.

episodes.title: Cold Stones
episodes.plot: Phil takes out his revenge on Vito, while Tony grows frustrated with Anthony Jr's lack of ambition or work ethic.

episodes.title: Kaisha
episodes.plot: Tony and Phil begin an explosive conflict that puts Phil in the hospital, while Christopher and Tony both embark on new romances with the same woman.

episodes.title: Soprano Home Movies
episodes.plot: Carmela and Tony go away to Bobby's cabin upstate New York for Tony's birthday up where a fight emerges between Tony and Bobby over Janice. Meanwhile A.J. is throwing a party at the Soprano home.

episodes.title: Stage 5
episodes.plot: Johnny Sac finds out he only has 3 months to live. Meanwhile, 'Cleaver' premieres and is a hit, while Carmela has mixed emotions about it, saying too much of it is based on Tony.

episodes.title: Remember When
episodes.plot: While forced to lay low in Miami, Tony begins to question Paulie's loyalty. Junior and Phil Leotardo both make moves to gain power in their respective territories.

episodes.title: Chasing It
episodes.plot: Tony hits an unlucky series of gambling losses, causing tension with both Carmela and Hesh. AJ and Blanca decide to make major changes in their relationship.

episodes.title: Walk Like a Man
episodes.plot: Christopher's father-in-law is the unwitting catalyst of a new feud between Christopher and Paulie. AJ struggles with depression.

episodes.title: Kennedy and Heidi
episodes.plot: Tony travels to Las Vegas after a tragedy occurs.

episodes.title: The Second Coming
episodes.plot: Tony fails to reason with Phil as more problems increase with Anthony Jr as his depression worsens.

episodes.title: The Blue Comet
episodes.plot: The allegiance of those closest to Tony is put to the test. A case of mistaken identity has serious ramifications.

episodes.title: Made in America
episodes.plot: Tony and his family have to stay in hiding until Phil Leotardo is dealt with. His family doesn't like the lifestyle they have been forced to adopt. AJ and Meadow move onto the next step in their lives. Tony confronts Junior one last time.
